'''Accolade''', n. [F. ''accolade'', It. ''accolata'', fr. ''accollare'' to [[embrace]]; L. ''ad'' + ''collum'' neck.]

<ol>
<li>A ceremony formerly used in [[conferring]] [[knighthood]], consisting of an embrace, and a slight blow on the shoulders with the flat blade of a sword.

<li> ''([[Mus (subject)|Mus]]).'' A brace used to join two or more [[staves]].
</ol>